WEBVTT

1
00:01:52.863 --> 00:01:53.864
Bingo.

2
00:02:09.130 --> 00:02:11.215
Fucking hell.

3
00:02:11.299 --> 00:02:12.883
[Screeches]

4
00:02:12.967 --> 00:02:15.386
Fucking hell.

5
00:02:15.469 --> 00:02:17.221
[Screeches]

6
00:03:05.478 --> 00:03:06.395
Oh. God.

7
00:03:06.479 --> 00:03:08.022
Keep your shit together...

8
00:03:08.105 --> 00:03:10.274
if you wanna get 'em out of here.

9
00:03:12.318 --> 00:03:13.778
I can pop these. no problem!

10
00:03:13.861 --> 00:03:14.820
So get to it!

11
00:03:29.085 --> 00:03:30.127
Security. we have a break-in.

12
00:03:30.211 --> 00:03:31.545
Get to sector—

13
00:03:39.845 --> 00:03:41.889
I know who you are.

14
00:03:41.972 --> 00:03:43.224
I know what you
think you're doing—

15
00:03:43.307 --> 00:03:44.266
If you don't wanna get hurt...

16
00:03:44.350 --> 00:03:45.309
keep your mouth shut...

17
00:03:45.393 --> 00:03:46.852
and don't move a fuckin'' muscle.

18
00:03:46.936 --> 00:03:48.396
The chimps are infected!

19
00:03:48.479 --> 00:03:50.981
They're highly contagious.

20
00:03:51.065 --> 00:03:52.191
They've been given an inhibitor.

21
00:03:52.274 --> 00:03:53.275
Infected with what?

22
00:03:53.359 --> 00:03:55.736
In order to cure.
you must first understand.

23
00:03:55.820 --> 00:03:57.571
Infected with what?!

24
00:04:00.574 --> 00:04:01.826
Rage.

25
00:04:04.245 --> 00:04:05.913
What the fuck he's talking about?!

26
00:04:05.996 --> 00:04:07.039
We don't have time for this!

27
00:04:07.123 --> 00:04:08.082
Get the cages open!

28
00:04:08.165 --> 00:04:09.583
No! No! No!

29
00:04:09.667 --> 00:04:11.502
Listen. you sick bastard.

30
00:04:11.585 --> 00:04:12.878
We're going. and we're taking...

31
00:04:12.962 --> 00:04:13.879
your torture victims with us.

32
00:04:13.963 --> 00:04:15.589
Woman: We're gonna
get you out of here.

33
00:04:15.673 --> 00:04:17.633
Listen. the animals are contagious.

34
00:04:17.716 --> 00:04:19.593
The infection is
in their blood and saliva.

35
00:04:19.677 --> 00:04:21.095
One bite—Stop!

36
00:04:21.178 --> 00:04:22.847
Stop!
You've no idea—

37
00:04:24.682 --> 00:04:25.599
Aah!

38
00:04:25.683 --> 00:04:27.268
Researcher: No!

39
00:04:29.019 --> 00:04:32.189
Get it off!
Oh. God! Help me!

40
00:04:32.273 --> 00:04:34.567
[All Shouting.
Monkeys Screeching]

41
00:04:37.194 --> 00:04:39.738
Get it off!
Get it off!

42
00:04:42.616 --> 00:04:43.868
<i>"M burning!</i>

43
00:04:43.951 --> 00:04:44.869
What the fuck is
the matter with her?!

44
00:04:44.952 --> 00:04:46.579
We have to kill her!

45
00:04:48.706 --> 00:04:50.958
Aah! Oh. my God!

46
00:04:51.041 --> 00:04:52.668
Aah!

47
00:04:54.462 --> 00:04:55.796
What's the matter with her?!

48
00:04:55.880 --> 00:04:57.423
We have to kill her now!

49
00:05:01.051 --> 00:05:02.553
Researcher: Oh. God.

50
00:06:32.726 --> 00:06:34.478
Aah.

51
00:06:50.995 --> 00:06:53.247
Hello?

52
00:07:10.347 --> 00:07:15.227
[Coughs]

53
00:07:31.201 --> 00:07:33.037
Hello?

54
00:07:51.221 --> 00:07:53.057
Hello?!

55
00:08:24.046 --> 00:08:25.255
[Belches]

56
00:09:34.742 --> 00:09:37.119
Hello?!

57
00:10:02.519 --> 00:10:04.897
Hello?!

58
00:11:59.636 --> 00:12:02.806
[Car Alarm Blaring]

59
00:14:56.480 --> 00:14:57.481
Hello?

60
00:15:00.859 --> 00:15:02.069
[Pounding On Door]

61
00:15:04.488 --> 00:15:06.406
[Pounding On Door]

62
00:15:06.490 --> 00:15:08.575
Hello?

63
00:15:08.658 --> 00:15:12.287
[Pounding Grows Louder]

64
00:15:17.793 --> 00:15:20.796
[Man Choking]

65
00:15:22.672 --> 00:15:23.715
Father?

66
00:15:31.681 --> 00:15:33.308
Father. are you okay?

67
00:15:40.941 --> 00:15:42.567
Oh. I shouldn't have done that.

68
00:15:43.819 --> 00:15:46.404
I shouldn't have done that.

69
00:15:46.488 --> 00:15:47.739
Shit!

70
00:16:15.225 --> 00:16:17.561
- Over here!
- Move it!

71
00:16:20.355 --> 00:16:21.982
Over here!

72
00:16:22.065 --> 00:16:23.900
Come on!

73
00:16:28.572 --> 00:16:30.157
Burn!

74
00:16:30.240 --> 00:16:32.159
Come on!

75
00:16:35.328 --> 00:16:37.080
Go! Go! Go!

76
00:16:43.044 --> 00:16:43.962
Keep going!

77
00:16:44.045 --> 00:16:45.255
What the fuck is going on?

78
00:16:45.338 --> 00:16:46.673
Just shut up!

79
00:16:55.974 --> 00:16:57.767
Who are those people?

80
00:17:16.953 --> 00:17:18.705
Wha-hoo!

81
00:17:25.003 --> 00:17:26.671
Let's go. Let's go!

82
00:17:26.755 --> 00:17:28.131
Please tell me what
the fuck is going on.

83
00:17:28.215 --> 00:17:29.674
Just move!

84
00:17:37.098 --> 00:17:38.475
Come on!

85
00:17:58.620 --> 00:18:01.539
A man walks into
a bar with a giraffe.

86
00:18:01.623 --> 00:18:05.043
They each get pissed.
The giraffe falls over.

87
00:18:05.126 --> 00:18:08.088
The man goes to leave.
The barman says. “Oi...

88
00:18:08.171 --> 00:18:10.590
you can't leave that lyin' there.”

89
00:18:10.674 --> 00:18:13.551
He says. “No. it's not a lion.

90
00:18:13.635 --> 00:18:16.763
It's a giraffe.”
[Sighs]

91
00:18:22.978 --> 00:18:25.313
He's completely humorless.

92
00:18:25.397 --> 00:18:27.691
You two should get on
like a house on fire.

93
00:18:29.442 --> 00:18:33.446
So. who are you?

94
00:18:33.530 --> 00:18:34.572
Well. you're from a hospital. yeah?

95
00:18:34.656 --> 00:18:35.782
You’re a doctor.

96
00:18:35.865 --> 00:18:37.909
He's not a doctor.
He's a patient.

97
00:18:37.993 --> 00:18:40.036
Look. I'm a bicycle courier.

98
00:18:40.120 --> 00:18:42.455
[Chuckles]

99
00:18:42.539 --> 00:18:46.459
I was riding a package
from. uh. Farringdon...

100
00:18:46.543 --> 00:18:49.587
to Shaftesbury Avenue
when a car cut across me.

101
00:18:49.671 --> 00:18:51.548
And then I wake up
today in hospital.

102
00:18:51.631 --> 00:18:53.633
I wake up. and I'm—

103
00:18:53.717 --> 00:18:55.552
I"m hallucinating. or I'm—

104
00:18:56.845 --> 00:18:58.388
What's your name?

105
00:18:58.471 --> 00:19:00.724
Jim.

106
00:19:01.975 --> 00:19:05.395
<i>'m Mark.
This is Selena.</i>

107
00:19:08.898 --> 00:19:11.234
Okay. Jim...

108
00:19:16.364 --> 00:19:17.782
I've got some bad news.

109
00:19:19.284 --> 00:19:21.661
It started as rioting...

110
00:19:21.745 --> 00:19:23.330
and right from the beginning...

111
00:19:23.413 --> 00:19:25.373
you knew this was different...

112
00:19:25.457 --> 00:19:26.458
because it was happening...

113
00:19:26.541 --> 00:19:30.170
in small villages. market towns.

114
00:19:30.253 --> 00:19:33.131
And then it wasn't
on the TV anymore.

115
00:19:33.214 --> 00:19:35.008
It was in the street outside...

116
00:19:35.091 --> 00:19:37.177
it was coming through your windows.

117
00:19:37.260 --> 00:19:41.431
It was a virus. an infection.

118
00:19:41.514 --> 00:19:44.517
You didn't need a doctor
to tell you that.

119
00:19:44.601 --> 00:19:46.853
It was the blood.

120
00:19:46.936 --> 00:19:50.440
Or something in the blood.

121
00:19:50.523 --> 00:19:53.026
By the time they tried
to evacuate the cities...

122
00:19:53.109 --> 00:19:56.071
it was already too late.

123
00:19:56.154 --> 00:19:58.531
The infection was everywhere.

124
00:19:58.615 --> 00:20:02.202
The army blockades were overrun.

125
00:20:02.285 --> 00:20:05.872
And that's when the exodus started.

126
00:20:07.665 --> 00:20:08.875
The day before the TV...

127
00:20:08.958 --> 00:20:10.377
and radio stopped broadcasting...

128
00:20:10.460 --> 00:20:11.711
there were reports of infection...

129
00:20:11.795 --> 00:20:13.713
in Paris and New York.

130
00:20:16.174 --> 00:20:18.968
You didn't hear
anything more after that.

131
00:20:22.472 --> 00:20:23.390
What about the government?

132
00:20:23.473 --> 00:20:24.391
What are they doing?

133
00:20:24.474 --> 00:20:25.767
There's no government.

134
00:20:25.850 --> 00:20:27.018
Of course there's a government.

135
00:20:27.102 --> 00:20:29.270
There's always a government.

136
00:20:29.354 --> 00:20:31.731
They're in a bunker or a plane.

137
00:20:31.815 --> 00:20:33.108
No. there's no government...

138
00:20:33.191 --> 00:20:34.526
no police...

139
00:20:34.609 --> 00:20:36.403
no army...

140
00:20:37.904 --> 00:20:40.949
no TV. no radio. no electricity.

141
00:20:41.032 --> 00:20:43.076
You're the first
uninfected person...

142
00:20:43.159 --> 00:20:45.120
we've seen in 6 days.

143
00:20:46.621 --> 00:20:47.539
Where's your family?

144
00:20:48.915 --> 00:20:52.001
They're dead. like Selena's...

145
00:20:52.085 --> 00:20:53.837
yours will be dead. too.

146
00:20:55.338 --> 00:20:56.589
No.

147
00:21:04.180 --> 00:21:05.098
Look. I have to find them.

148
00:21:05.181 --> 00:21:06.307
They live in Deptford.

149
00:21:06.391 --> 00:21:08.059
I can walk it. okay?

150
00:21:08.143 --> 00:21:09.894
What. you'll go and come back. yeah?

151
00:21:09.978 --> 00:21:12.772
Get the fucking—Fuck!

152
00:21:12.856 --> 00:21:14.607
-You won't!
- Yes!

153
00:21:14.691 --> 00:21:16.609
No one ever comes back.

154
00:21:22.449 --> 00:21:25.743
So. lesson one;

155
00:21:25.827 --> 00:21:27.245
You never go anywhere alone...

156
00:21:27.328 --> 00:21:29.998
unless you've got no choice.

157
00:21:30.081 --> 00:21:34.085
And lesson 2: Only
travel during daylight...

158
00:21:34.169 --> 00:21:35.670
unless you've got no choice.

159
00:21:38.923 --> 00:21:40.633
We'll take you tomorrow.

160
00:21:40.717 --> 00:21:43.428
We'll all go and find
your dead parents together. okay?

161
00:21:45.221 --> 00:21:46.848
Eat.

162
00:21:50.977 --> 00:21:54.147
♪♪ [Woman Singing Hymn]

163
00:21:59.194 --> 00:22:00.570
Mark: If you want to slow down...

164
00:22:00.653 --> 00:22:02.071
you'll have to say.

165
00:22:02.155 --> 00:22:08.036
♪♪ [Continues]

166
00:22:21.925 --> 00:22:26.346
♪♪ [Continues]

167
00:22:28.848 --> 00:22:30.183
Selena: If there's
anyone in there who is—

168
00:22:30.266 --> 00:22:31.184
Jim: I understand.

169
00:22:31.267 --> 00:22:32.185
Anyone.

170
00:22:32.268 --> 00:22:33.186
I understand.

171
00:22:34.437 --> 00:22:36.397
Mark: Okay.

172
00:22:43.530 --> 00:22:49.869
♪♪ [Continues]

173
00:23:08.471 --> 00:23:13.309
♪♪ [Continues]

174
00:23:18.147 --> 00:23:20.608
Jim.

175
00:23:20.692 --> 00:23:22.610
Wait. Jim.

176
00:23:25.989 --> 00:23:28.324
♪♪ [Continues]

177
00:23:32.912 --> 00:23:34.914
♪♪ [Stops]

178
00:24:01.232 --> 00:24:03.234
♪♪ [Resumes]

179
00:24:21.919 --> 00:24:26.633
♪♪ [Continues]

180
00:24:40.772 --> 00:24:46.694
♪♪ [Ends]

181
00:24:46.778 --> 00:24:49.030
They died peacefully.

182
00:24:49.113 --> 00:24:50.615
You should be grateful.

183
00:24:50.698 --> 00:24:52.158
<i>'M not grateful.</i>

184
00:24:54.410 --> 00:24:57.080
Mark: My. um...

185
00:24:57.163 --> 00:24:59.707
parents and my sisters...

186
00:24:59.791 --> 00:25:03.961
we went to Paddington Station...

187
00:25:04.045 --> 00:25:05.880
hoping maybe we
could get on a plane...

188
00:25:05.963 --> 00:25:09.509
maybe we could buy
our way onto a plane.

189
00:25:09.592 --> 00:25:12.804
I remember my dad
had all this cash...

190
00:25:12.887 --> 00:25:16.808
even though cash
was completely useless.

191
00:25:16.891 --> 00:25:18.935
About 20.000 other people...

192
00:25:19.018 --> 00:25:21.104
had the same idea.

193
00:25:22.980 --> 00:25:25.692
The crowd was surging.

194
00:25:25.775 --> 00:25:30.154
I lost my grip on my sister's hand.

195
00:25:30.238 --> 00:25:34.659
I remember the ground was soft.

196
00:25:34.742 --> 00:25:36.869
I looked down. and I was standing...

197
00:25:36.953 --> 00:25:40.206
on all these people.
like a carpet...

198
00:25:40.289 --> 00:25:42.125
people who had fallen.

199
00:25:42.208 --> 00:25:44.252
And somewhere in the crowd...

200
00:25:44.335 --> 00:25:46.879
there were infected.
It spread fast.

201
00:25:46.963 --> 00:25:48.881
No one could run.

202
00:25:48.965 --> 00:25:52.051
All you could do was climb...

203
00:25:52.135 --> 00:25:54.554
climb over more people.
So I did that...

204
00:25:54.637 --> 00:25:58.349
I climbed. and I got up
on top of this kiosk.

205
00:26:00.476 --> 00:26:01.519
Looking down. you couldn't tell...

206
00:26:01.602 --> 00:26:03.062
which faces were infected...

207
00:26:03.146 --> 00:26:04.897
and which weren't.

208
00:26:04.981 --> 00:26:06.649
Then I saw my dad...

209
00:26:06.733 --> 00:26:11.237
not my mum or my sister. my dad.

210
00:26:13.239 --> 00:26:16.159
His face.

211
00:26:19.328 --> 00:26:21.873
Selena's right.

212
00:26:21.956 --> 00:26:23.124
You should be grateful.

213
00:26:23.207 --> 00:26:24.125
We don't have time...

214
00:26:24.208 --> 00:26:26.043
to get back to the shop before dark.

215
00:26:26.127 --> 00:26:27.837
We should stay here tonight.

216
00:26:31.507 --> 00:26:33.134
My room is up at the top.
You two can have that.

217
00:26:33.217 --> 00:26:34.135
I'll stay here.

218
00:26:34.218 --> 00:26:35.803
No. we'll all sleep
in the same room.

219
00:26:35.887 --> 00:26:37.346
It's safer.

220
00:27:13.549 --> 00:27:15.510
[Tape Playing Low]

221
00:27:48.709 --> 00:27:49.752
Tape: It was recorded...

222
00:27:49.836 --> 00:27:51.879
at the Buxton Summer
Music Festival last July...

223
00:27:51.963 --> 00:27:54.590
and it's presented
by Petrov Trelawny.

224
00:27:57.134 --> 00:27:58.094
Jim.

225
00:28:08.563 --> 00:28:09.480
Ah. you're back.

226
00:28:09.564 --> 00:28:10.481
Yeah.

227
00:28:16.821 --> 00:28:17.738
How was it?

228
00:28:17.822 --> 00:28:19.490
Fine.

229
00:28:19.574 --> 00:28:21.993
Give me a drink of that. will you?

230
00:28:22.076 --> 00:28:23.494
It’s empty.

231
00:28:23.578 --> 00:28:24.495
Ah.

232
00:28:26.330 --> 00:28:27.248
Here.

233
00:28:27.331 --> 00:28:29.125
Right.

234
00:28:30.793 --> 00:28:33.296
Father: I'll start
working on them. then.

235
00:28:39.802 --> 00:28:42.263
Mark: Fight! Fight!

236
00:28:42.346 --> 00:28:43.556
Selena!

237
00:28:58.988 --> 00:29:00.656
Selena: It's clear.

238
00:29:06.329 --> 00:29:07.580
That's Mr. Bridges.

239
00:29:07.663 --> 00:29:08.998
Were you bitten?

240
00:29:09.081 --> 00:29:11.083
That's his daughter.

241
00:29:11.167 --> 00:29:12.084
They live 4 doors down.

242
00:29:12.168 --> 00:29:13.377
Were you bitten?

243
00:29:13.461 --> 00:29:15.254
No.

244
00:29:15.338 --> 00:29:17.340
Did any of the blood
get in your mouth?

245
00:29:18.549 --> 00:29:20.009
No.

246
00:29:24.055 --> 00:29:25.014
Mark?

247
00:29:28.059 --> 00:29:29.018
Wait.

248
00:29:52.041 --> 00:29:53.542
Get that cleaned off.

249
00:29:55.670 --> 00:29:57.213
Do you have any clothes here?

250
00:29:59.090 --> 00:30:01.592
Um. 
—yes.

251
00:30:01.676 --> 00:30:02.969
Then get them and get dressed.

252
00:30:03.052 --> 00:30:04.303
We have to leave now.

253
00:30:04.387 --> 00:30:07.223
More infected will be coming.

254
00:30:07.306 --> 00:30:09.016
They always do.

255
00:30:37.294 --> 00:30:38.629
Jim: How did you know?

256
00:30:38.713 --> 00:30:40.673
I mean. how did you know
he was infected?

257
00:30:40.756 --> 00:30:41.674
Selena: The blood.

258
00:30:41.757 --> 00:30:43.050
Yeah. but there
was blood everywhere.

259
00:30:43.134 --> 00:30:44.719
It was on me.
It was on you.

260
00:30:44.802 --> 00:30:46.512
I didn't know he was infected. okay?

261
00:30:46.595 --> 00:30:48.764
He knew.
I could see it in his face.

262
00:30:50.057 --> 00:30:51.600
Look. if someone gets infected...

263
00:30:51.684 --> 00:30:53.978
you've got between
10 and 20 seconds to kill them.

264
00:30:54.061 --> 00:30:56.647
It might be your brother
or your sister...

265
00:30:56.731 --> 00:30:57.732
or your oldest friend.

266
00:30:57.815 --> 00:30:59.692
It makes no difference.

267
00:30:59.775 --> 00:31:00.860
And just so you know
where you stand...

268
00:31:00.943 --> 00:31:03.571
if it happens to you.
I'll do it in a heartbeat.

269
00:31:05.489 --> 00:31:07.992
He was full of plans.

270
00:31:08.075 --> 00:31:09.368
Have you got any plans. Jim?

271
00:31:09.452 --> 00:31:11.454
Do you want us to find
a cure and save the world...

272
00:31:11.537 --> 00:31:13.789
or just fall in love and fuck?

273
00:31:13.873 --> 00:31:15.541
Plans are pointless.

274
00:31:15.624 --> 00:31:16.667
[Sniffs]

275
00:31:16.751 --> 00:31:19.045
Staying alive's as good as it gets.

276
00:31:20.921 --> 00:31:22.715
Hey. hey. hey. hey. hey. hey.

277
00:31:22.798 --> 00:31:23.716
what’s that?

278
00:31:30.473 --> 00:31:31.390
Selena: Let's go.

279
00:32:16.727 --> 00:32:19.355
What is it about tower blocks...

280
00:32:19.438 --> 00:32:21.398
and shopping trolleys. huh?

281
00:32:21.482 --> 00:32:23.609
Stop talking.
It's a long way up.

282
00:32:33.494 --> 00:32:35.246
Selena: Do you need a break?

283
00:32:35.329 --> 00:32:36.247
No.

284
00:32:37.665 --> 00:32:39.041
-You?
- No.

285
00:32:41.836 --> 00:32:45.381
Now I do need a break...
by the way.

286
00:32:54.306 --> 00:32:56.475
What's up?

287
00:32:56.559 --> 00:32:57.893
Nothin'.

288
00:32:57.977 --> 00:32:59.228
[Sighs]

289
00:33:01.063 --> 00:33:02.273
Got a headache.

290
00:33:02.356 --> 00:33:03.482
Bad?

291
00:33:03.566 --> 00:33:04.525
Yeah. it’s pretty bad.

292
00:33:04.608 --> 00:33:06.277
Well. why didn't you
say something before?

293
00:33:06.360 --> 00:33:08.237
Well. because I didn't think
you'd give a shit.

294
00:33:10.739 --> 00:33:12.324
You've got no fat on you...

295
00:33:12.408 --> 00:33:14.910
and all you've
had to eat is sugar...

296
00:33:14.994 --> 00:33:16.662
so you're crashing.

297
00:33:16.745 --> 00:33:18.122
Unfortunately. there isn't a lot...

298
00:33:18.205 --> 00:33:19.248
we can do about that...

299
00:33:19.331 --> 00:33:21.041
except pump you
full of painkillers...

300
00:33:21.125 --> 00:33:22.042
and give you more sugar.

301
00:33:22.126 --> 00:33:28.174
As for sugar. Pepsi or Lilt?

302
00:33:28.257 --> 00:33:30.301
Do you have any Tango?

303
00:33:30.384 --> 00:33:33.220
Actually. I did have
a can of Tango somewhere.

304
00:33:33.304 --> 00:33:34.221
[Screeching]

305
00:33:34.305 --> 00:33:36.765
Quiet! That's an infected.

306
00:33:38.350 --> 00:33:40.561
[Snarling]

307
00:33:47.193 --> 00:33:48.944
Oh. no. They're in. Move!

308
00:33:52.072 --> 00:33:53.115
Jim: Wait. Selena!

309
00:33:55.409 --> 00:33:56.869
Wait for me. please!

310
00:33:56.952 --> 00:33:58.871
Wait. Selena!

311
00:33:58.954 --> 00:34:01.832
Please wait for me!

312
00:34:01.916 --> 00:34:03.000
- Selena!
- Come on!

313
00:34:03.083 --> 00:34:04.210
- Wait!
- Run!

314
00:34:04.293 --> 00:34:07.671
Wait. for fuck's sake!

315
00:34:07.755 --> 00:34:09.131
Selena!

316
00:34:09.215 --> 00:34:10.382
Aah!

317
00:34:12.176 --> 00:34:14.136
Down the corridor. flat 157!

318
00:34:14.220 --> 00:34:15.512
Move!

319
00:34:15.596 --> 00:34:16.764
Jim: Thank you!
Thank you!

320
00:34:29.818 --> 00:34:30.986
Open the door!

321
00:34:37.785 --> 00:34:39.328
Open the door!

322
00:34:43.457 --> 00:34:44.959
Open up!

323
00:34:45.042 --> 00:34:46.835
Where's Dad?
What?!

324
00:34:50.673 --> 00:34:51.548
Open the fucking door!

325
00:34:51.632 --> 00:34:52.925
Where's Dad?!

326
00:34:53.008 --> 00:34:54.093
Fucking open the door!

327
00:34:54.176 --> 00:34:56.011
Hannah. let them inside.

328
00:35:03.435 --> 00:35:05.020
Go In.

329
00:35:05.104 --> 00:35:06.480
Go In.

330
00:35:07.940 --> 00:35:11.986
[Music Box Playing Christmas Song]

331
00:35:24.206 --> 00:35:26.333
So. I'm Frank. anyway.

332
00:35:26.417 --> 00:35:27.376
Jim.

333
00:35:29.503 --> 00:35:30.879
Selena.

334
00:35:30.963 --> 00:35:32.548
Selena. good to meet you.

335
00:35:32.631 --> 00:35:34.383
This is my daughter Hannah.

336
00:35:34.466 --> 00:35:36.552
Come on. sweetheart.
Say hello.

337
00:35:38.804 --> 00:35:39.722
Come on.

338
00:35:41.640 --> 00:35:43.642
So—

339
00:35:43.726 --> 00:35:45.477
This is great.
It's just great.

340
00:35:47.855 --> 00:35:50.316
Calls for a celebration. I'd say.

341
00:35:50.399 --> 00:35:51.942
Why don't you all sit down...

342
00:35:52.026 --> 00:35:55.821
and. uh. Hannah. what
have we got to offer?

343
00:35:55.904 --> 00:35:58.490
We've got Mum's créme de men the.

344
00:35:58.574 --> 00:36:00.784
Great.
Her créme de men the.

345
00:36:00.868 --> 00:36:02.745
Aye.

346
00:36:02.828 --> 00:36:04.288
Look. sit. please.

347
00:36:04.371 --> 00:36:05.914
Get comfortable.

348
00:36:09.752 --> 00:36:11.462
Frank: Where are
the bloody glasses?!

349
00:36:11.545 --> 00:36:12.880
Middle cupboard.

350
00:36:12.963 --> 00:36:15.841
No. the good ones.
It's a celebration.

351
00:36:15.924 --> 00:36:16.842
Top cupboard.

352
00:36:16.925 --> 00:36:19.595
So...50. this is your place?

353
00:36:22.639 --> 00:36:24.183
It's nice.

354
00:36:32.149 --> 00:36:33.108
Yeah.

355
00:36:37.071 --> 00:36:38.447
Now...

356
00:36:38.530 --> 00:36:41.241
I know it isn't much.
but. well. cheers.

357
00:36:41.325 --> 00:36:43.452
Cheers.

358
00:36:50.876 --> 00:36:51.794
[Music Box Stops Playing]

359
00:36:58.175 --> 00:37:00.761
[Groans]

360
00:37:04.973 --> 00:37:06.225
You okay in there. Jim?

361
00:37:08.018 --> 00:37:08.977
Yeah.

362
00:37:10.479 --> 00:37:12.815
Sorry we couldn't spare the water.

363
00:37:12.898 --> 00:37:13.899
Same with the toilet.

364
00:37:13.982 --> 00:37:16.026
The. um. flush doesn't work.

365
00:37:17.653 --> 00:37:19.321
Afraid you'll have
to use the bucket.

366
00:37:26.370 --> 00:37:29.248
Have to empty it
each morning. you know.

367
00:37:29.331 --> 00:37:30.833
Just chuck it over the balcony.

368
00:37:30.916 --> 00:37:32.251
No mod cons here.

369
00:37:32.334 --> 00:37:34.211
Yeah. It's fine.

370
00:37:34.294 --> 00:37:35.587
Yeah. all right. listen...

371
00:37:35.671 --> 00:37:37.339
it's late.
I"m gonna turn in.

372
00:37:38.924 --> 00:37:42.803
We have a spare room...

373
00:37:42.886 --> 00:37:44.263
in there.

374
00:37:44.346 --> 00:37:46.348
Are you and Selena—

375
00:37:47.599 --> 00:37:49.393
Oh. no. No. no. no.

376
00:37:49.476 --> 00:37:53.689
Um. no. I'll take
the living room. It's fine.

377
00:37:53.772 --> 00:37:54.690
Right.

378
00:37:56.525 --> 00:37:57.943
Oh. no. I mean. yeah.

379
00:37:59.695 --> 00:38:02.072
Yeah. so. um. all right.

380
00:38:02.156 --> 00:38:03.824
Okay. good night. then. anyway.

381
00:38:03.907 --> 00:38:05.534
Yeah. good night. Frank.

382
00:38:13.041 --> 00:38:14.042
[Door Opens]

383
00:38:19.715 --> 00:38:21.842
Very spruce.

384
00:38:21.925 --> 00:38:24.553
Yeah...
very shredded.

385
00:38:24.636 --> 00:38:25.554
Yeah.

386
00:38:29.892 --> 00:38:32.019
So what do you make of them?

387
00:38:32.102 --> 00:38:35.022
Well. they're desperate.

388
00:38:35.105 --> 00:38:37.024
Probably need us
more than we need them.

389
00:38:39.526 --> 00:38:41.528
I think they're good people.

390
00:38:44.573 --> 00:38:45.657
Good people?

391
00:38:45.741 --> 00:38:46.867
Yeah.

392
00:38:49.411 --> 00:38:50.329
Well. that's nice...

393
00:38:50.412 --> 00:38:51.413
but you should be more concerned...

394
00:38:51.497 --> 00:38:54.041
about whether
they're gonna slow you down.

395
00:38:54.124 --> 00:38:56.376
Right. because if
they slowed you down—

396
00:38:56.460 --> 00:38:57.878
I'd leave them behind.

397
00:38:57.961 --> 00:38:59.838
- In a heartbeat.
- Yeah.

398
00:38:59.922 --> 00:39:02.257
I wouldn't.

399
00:39:02.341 --> 00:39:04.927
Then you're gonna wind up
getting yourself killed.

400
00:39:14.269 --> 00:39:15.395
<i>'M gonna get some sleep.</i>

401
00:39:18.982 --> 00:39:21.443
Selena...

402
00:39:21.527 --> 00:39:23.362
you think I don't get it...

403
00:39:23.445 --> 00:39:25.239
but. um. I do get it.

404
00:39:27.282 --> 00:39:28.867
And I know I'd be dead already...

405
00:39:28.951 --> 00:39:31.036
if I hadn't met you.

406
00:39:31.119 --> 00:39:32.079
Sure.

407
00:39:33.247 --> 00:39:34.790
No. look...

408
00:39:36.667 --> 00:39:39.002
I mean thank you.

409
00:39:42.464 --> 00:39:44.633
And I mean sure.

410
00:39:44.716 --> 00:39:46.385
Good night. Jim.

411
00:39:46.468 --> 00:39:48.303
Good night.

412
00:40:03.235 --> 00:40:04.903
Frank: We lost water pressure
3 weeks ago.

413
00:40:04.987 --> 00:40:06.321
For a while.
I thought we'd be okay...

414
00:40:06.405 --> 00:40:07.739
with the water in the other flats...

415
00:40:07.823 --> 00:40:09.157
cisterns. and tanks...

416
00:40:09.241 --> 00:40:11.994
but it vanishes so quick.
you wouldn't believe.

417
00:40:16.039 --> 00:40:19.376
You drink it.
It evaporates...

418
00:40:19.459 --> 00:40:21.003
turns stagnant.

419
00:40:24.089 --> 00:40:25.465
They're all empty.

420
00:40:27.551 --> 00:40:29.261
Hasn't rained in 10 days.

421
00:40:29.344 --> 00:40:30.929
You can set up a plastic sheet...

422
00:40:31.013 --> 00:40:32.472
to catch dew and condensation...

423
00:40:32.556 --> 00:40:33.890
trap it somehow.

424
00:40:33.974 --> 00:40:38.061
I saw it on TV once.
but I can't make it work.

425
00:40:38.145 --> 00:40:41.648
You'd never think it...

426
00:40:41.732 --> 00:40:43.859
needing rain so badly.

427
00:40:46.153 --> 00:40:48.780
Not in fucking England.

428
00:40:53.493 --> 00:40:56.997
Jim. we're not gonna
be able to stay here.

429
00:41:02.210 --> 00:41:05.631
[Radio Chatters]

430
00:41:05.714 --> 00:41:07.716
Selena: There haven't been
any broadcasts for weeks.

431
00:41:07.799 --> 00:41:08.967
Just listen.

432
00:41:09.051 --> 00:41:10.636
Man On Radio: ...Salvation is here.

433
00:41:10.719 --> 00:41:13.847
The answer to infection is here.

434
00:41:13.930 --> 00:41:16.975
If you can hear this.
you're not alone.

435
00:41:17.059 --> 00:41:18.727
There are others like you.

436
00:41:18.810 --> 00:41:21.980
There are fighters. other survivors.

437
00:41:22.064 --> 00:41:23.899
We are soldiers. and we are armed.

438
00:41:23.982 --> 00:41:27.444
Selena: Oh. my God. Soldiers.

439
00:41:27.527 --> 00:41:28.612
Quiet. There's more.

440
00:41:28.695 --> 00:41:30.155
Man On Radio: Our location
is the 42nd Blockade...

441
00:41:30.238 --> 00:41:35.619
the M602. 27 miles
northeast of Manchester.

442
00:41:35.702 --> 00:41:37.746
You must find us.
Salvation is—

443
00:41:37.829 --> 00:41:39.247
Then it just repeats.

444
00:41:39.331 --> 00:41:40.957
What. so it's a recording?

445
00:41:41.041 --> 00:41:42.000
Yeah. it's a recording...

446
00:41:42.084 --> 00:41:44.461
but this is where
it's telling us to go.

447
00:41:44.544 --> 00:41:47.172
Just there.

448
00:41:48.924 --> 00:41:49.883
The way things are...

449
00:41:49.966 --> 00:41:52.928
we might need
2. 3 days to get up there.

450
00:41:53.011 --> 00:41:55.097
Um [
. “'we”?

451
00:41:59.309 --> 00:42:00.727
Sound carries in this flat.

452
00:42:00.811 --> 00:42:02.270
You know. Jerry-built. I suppose.

453
00:42:02.354 --> 00:42:04.356
Me and Hannah do need you...

454
00:42:04.439 --> 00:42:05.482
more than you need us.

455
00:42:05.565 --> 00:42:06.608
Look. I didn't—

456
00:42:06.692 --> 00:42:08.568
That's okay.
It's the truth.

457
00:42:08.652 --> 00:42:09.569
I can't leave the block...

458
00:42:09.653 --> 00:42:11.029
if it's just the two of us.

459
00:42:11.113 --> 00:42:12.447
Something might happen to me.

460
00:42:12.531 --> 00:42:14.282
Hannah'd be alone.
I couldn't risk it...

461
00:42:15.325 --> 00:42:17.119
but with other people—

462
00:42:17.202 --> 00:42:19.037
If it's a recording.
for all we know...

463
00:42:19.121 --> 00:42:21.415
the soldiers who made it are dead.

464
00:42:21.498 --> 00:42:22.541
It's possible. yeah.

465
00:42:22.624 --> 00:42:24.918
And that stuff
about the answer to infection...

466
00:42:25.001 --> 00:42:27.170
I mean. there ls no answer
to infection.

467
00:42:27.254 --> 00:42:29.172
It's already done pretty much
all the damage it can.

468
00:42:29.256 --> 00:42:30.173
Maybe they have a cure.

469
00:42:30.257 --> 00:42:32.634
Maybe they've got nothing at all.

470
00:42:32.718 --> 00:42:34.428
Well. the only way to
find out is to reach them!

471
00:42:34.511 --> 00:42:36.555
We could die trying. Frank!

472
00:42:38.306 --> 00:42:40.642
Or die here...

473
00:42:40.726 --> 00:42:43.979
and anyway. it isn't
true what Dad said.

474
00:42:44.062 --> 00:42:46.732
You need us just the
same as we need you.

475
00:42:48.275 --> 00:42:50.110
We need each other...

476
00:42:50.193 --> 00:42:52.320
and we'll never be
safe in the cities.

477
00:42:52.404 --> 00:42:53.655
The soldiers could keep us safe.

478
00:42:55.574 --> 00:42:58.952
So we have to try and get there.

479
00:42:59.035 --> 00:43:01.079
Get there how?

480
00:43:12.174 --> 00:43:13.842
Just so you know...

481
00:43:13.925 --> 00:43:16.178
I don't take checks or credit cards.

482
00:43:16.261 --> 00:43:18.180
[Chuckles]

483
00:43:44.372 --> 00:43:45.624
Frank: What do you think?

484
00:43:45.707 --> 00:43:46.708
Well. it's the most direct route...

485
00:43:46.792 --> 00:43:47.834
to the other side of the river.

486
00:43:47.918 --> 00:43:49.044
No. no. no. then we should take...

487
00:43:49.127 --> 00:43:50.086
the indirect route...

488
00:43:50.170 --> 00:43:51.546
the one that's in broad daylight...

489
00:43:51.630 --> 00:43:53.131
and that's not underground.

490
00:43:53.215 --> 00:43:54.424
Frank: Let's just get it done.

491
00:44:08.271 --> 00:44:10.398
Jim: No. no.

492
00:44:10.482 --> 00:44:13.193
No. see. this is a really shit idea.

493
00:44:13.276 --> 00:44:14.653
You know why?

494
00:44:14.736 --> 00:44:17.489
Because it's really
obviously a shit idea.

495
00:44:17.572 --> 00:44:19.699
So. we're just gonna
drive into a tunnel...

496
00:44:19.783 --> 00:44:22.285
full of fuckin' smashed
cars and broken glass.

497
00:44:22.369 --> 00:44:24.955
It's just really fucking
obviously a shit idea!

498
00:44:25.038 --> 00:44:26.081
Hold on!

499
00:44:36.466 --> 00:44:37.592
Hannah: Dad!

500
00:44:40.303 --> 00:44:41.596
- Aah!
- Whoa!

501
00:44:41.680 --> 00:44:44.599
[All Laugh]

502
00:44:57.404 --> 00:44:58.363
Fuck!

503
00:45:00.115 --> 00:45:02.617
World's worst place
to get a flat. huh?

504
00:45:02.701 --> 00:45:03.827
Agreed.

505
00:45:03.910 --> 00:45:05.370
I think we better do this quick.

506
00:45:08.957 --> 00:45:11.084
Frank: I've got the wheel.
You’re on the jack.

507
00:45:21.469 --> 00:45:23.263
[Scuttling]

508
00:45:25.724 --> 00:45:27.100
Hey. did you hear that?
Hey. hey.

509
00:45:27.183 --> 00:45:29.269
Did you hear that?

510
00:45:29.352 --> 00:45:30.312
Hear what?

511
00:45:31.855 --> 00:45:33.440
Hannah: Right. I've done it.

512
00:45:35.525 --> 00:45:37.485
Dad?

513
00:45:37.569 --> 00:45:41.239
[Scuttling]

514
00:45:41.323 --> 00:45:43.033
Jim: Jesus Christ!

515
00:45:43.116 --> 00:45:45.994
Oh. no!
Fucking rats!

516
00:45:46.077 --> 00:45:47.120
Aah!

517
00:45:47.203 --> 00:45:49.164
Frank: Come on. Hannah. out! Out!

518
00:45:56.546 --> 00:45:59.591
They're running from the infected.

519
00:45:59.674 --> 00:46:01.426
Move it!

520
00:46:01.509 --> 00:46:02.385
Frank: Forget the jack. Hannah!

521
00:46:02.469 --> 00:46:03.428
Selena: Don't look at them!

522
00:46:03.511 --> 00:46:04.387
Frank: There's no time!
Forget the jack!

523
00:46:04.471 --> 00:46:05.597
Just lift. everyone!

524
00:46:05.680 --> 00:46:06.640
Grab hold!

525
00:46:06.723 --> 00:46:09.017
[Infected
Screeching]

526
00:46:09.100 --> 00:46:11.186
Lift!

527
00:46:13.188 --> 00:46:14.773
Lift! Lift!

528
00:46:14.856 --> 00:46:17.651
Selena: Don't look at them!
Don't look at them!

529
00:46:17.734 --> 00:46:20.445
Jim: I can see them!
They're coming! Aah!

530
00:46:20.528 --> 00:46:23.782
[Screeching]

531
00:46:25.992 --> 00:46:27.410
Selena; Come on. Hannah!

532
00:46:27.494 --> 00:46:28.828
Put it on!

533
00:46:28.912 --> 00:46:30.163
Hannah: Almost!

534
00:46:31.373 --> 00:46:32.749
Jim: Get the tire on. Hannah!

535
00:46:32.832 --> 00:46:34.209
- All right!
- Get it on. Hannah!

536
00:46:39.089 --> 00:46:42.342
Hannah: 3...2...1.
Drop it!

537
00:46:44.427 --> 00:46:46.680
Jim: Inside. everyone!
Inside!

538
00:46:46.763 --> 00:46:50.016
Selena; Get in the cab!
Get in the cab!

539
00:46:50.100 --> 00:46:51.559
Jim: Get in the fucking cab!

540
00:46:51.643 --> 00:46:53.186
Selena: Frank. drive!

541
00:46:54.646 --> 00:46:56.523
Hannah: Aah!

542
00:46:56.606 --> 00:46:59.442
Jim: Whoo!

543
00:47:04.197 --> 00:47:07.701
Jim: Bye-bye. you fuckers! Whoo!

544
00:47:14.457 --> 00:47:16.334
Selena: Hey. Frank.
Frank. stop the cab.

545
00:47:39.566 --> 00:47:41.026
Let's shop.

546
00:47:48.533 --> 00:47:49.701
<i>Rt!</i>

547
00:47:49.784 --> 00:47:51.578
<i>Rt!</i>

548
00:47:51.661 --> 00:47:52.620
[Laughs]

549
00:47:52.704 --> 00:47:54.748
You...

550
00:47:54.831 --> 00:47:56.374
You...

551
00:47:56.458 --> 00:47:57.876
You...

552
00:47:57.959 --> 00:48:00.545
Jim: Has anybody seen any buns?

553
00:48:00.628 --> 00:48:03.882
Mmm. Irradiated.

554
00:48:07.135 --> 00:48:10.472
And don't take anything
that needs to be cooked. okay?

555
00:48:10.555 --> 00:48:11.931
I think you can eat that raw.

556
00:48:12.015 --> 00:48:14.059
Decaffeinated coffee.

557
00:48:14.142 --> 00:48:15.101
Frank: Put that back.

558
00:48:17.312 --> 00:48:19.773
Can't just take any crap.

559
00:48:19.856 --> 00:48:21.649
If I never see
another chocolate bar again...

560
00:48:21.733 --> 00:48:23.526
it will be too soon.

561
00:48:23.610 --> 00:48:24.861
[Gasps]

562
00:48:24.944 --> 00:48:27.363
Not counting Terry's
chocolate orange. of course!

563
00:48:27.447 --> 00:48:29.115
There.

564
00:48:29.199 --> 00:48:31.618
Now. single malt. 16-year-old.

565
00:48:31.701 --> 00:48:33.578
Dark. full-flavor.

566
00:48:33.661 --> 00:48:35.789
Warm. but not aggressive.

567
00:48:35.872 --> 00:48:39.125
Peaty aftertaste.

568
00:48:39.209 --> 00:48:40.627
Yeah.

569
00:48:40.710 --> 00:48:43.505
Takes out the fire.
but leaves in the warmth.

570
00:48:43.588 --> 00:48:45.632
[Women Laugh]

571
00:49:00.980 --> 00:49:01.898
Ha ha ha.

572
00:49:05.568 --> 00:49:09.322
[All Laugh]

573
00:49:36.224 --> 00:49:38.810
[Engine Stops]

574
00:49:38.893 --> 00:49:41.896
Either we do this now.
or we're walking.

575
00:49:48.611 --> 00:49:49.904
Frank: Not you.

576
00:49:53.908 --> 00:49:55.368
Stay close. Jim.

577
00:49:55.451 --> 00:49:56.911
What?

578
00:49:56.995 --> 00:49:57.912
You heard me.

579
00:50:25.023 --> 00:50:26.733
Where are you going?

580
00:50:28.693 --> 00:50:30.695
We've got enough food. Jim.

581
00:50:30.778 --> 00:50:33.114
We don't have any cheeseburgers.

582
00:50:34.324 --> 00:50:36.784
Like going on holidays
with your fuckin' aunt.

583
00:51:16.074 --> 00:51:18.493
Oh. Jesus.

584
00:51:43.935 --> 00:51:45.687
Hello?

585
00:51:59.492 --> 00:52:00.827
I hate you!

586
00:52:10.753 --> 00:52:11.838
Find anything?

587
00:52:14.924 --> 00:52:16.009
Find anything. Jim?

588
00:52:16.092 --> 00:52:17.343
No. Let's get out of here.

589
00:52:17.427 --> 00:52:18.845
Okay. we're done here.

590
00:52:21.931 --> 00:52:22.890
Okay. Hannah!

591
00:52:22.974 --> 00:52:24.809
[Engine Starts]

592
00:52:30.857 --> 00:52:35.236
Steady. Easy. Brake.
Brake! Brake!

593
00:52:42.827 --> 00:52:43.745
Out.

594
00:53:29.165 --> 00:53:30.708
Selena: Mmm!

595
00:53:30.792 --> 00:53:33.753
Oh. my God!

596
00:53:33.836 --> 00:53:36.464
I can. like. taste the vitamin “C.”

597
00:53:37.590 --> 00:53:41.219
[Muffled]
Okay. the raisins are still moist.

598
00:53:41.302 --> 00:53:43.846
What did you say?

599
00:53:43.930 --> 00:53:45.223
[Muffled]
The raisins. yeah?

600
00:53:45.306 --> 00:53:47.642
They're still moist.

601
00:53:47.725 --> 00:53:49.143
[All Giggle]

602
00:53:51.312 --> 00:53:52.313
Look over here.

603
00:54:02.323 --> 00:54:04.617
[Horse Neighs]

604
00:54:04.700 --> 00:54:06.077
Like a family.

605
00:54:06.160 --> 00:54:09.080
Hannah: Do you think
they're infected?

606
00:54:09.163 --> 00:54:10.081
Frank: No.

607
00:54:14.460 --> 00:54:16.462
They're doing just fine.

608
00:54:22.969 --> 00:54:25.346
Come on. Let's eat!

609
00:54:26.639 --> 00:54:29.725
[Horse Neighs]

610
00:54:40.820 --> 00:54:41.904
Jim: Do you know
what I was thinking?

611
00:54:41.988 --> 00:54:42.989
Selena: You were thinking
that you'll never hear...

612
00:54:43.072 --> 00:54:45.366
another piece of
original music ever again.

613
00:54:45.450 --> 00:54:47.452
You'll never read a book...

614
00:54:47.535 --> 00:54:50.705
that hasn't already been written...

615
00:54:50.788 --> 00:54:54.584
or see a film that hasn't
already been shot.

616
00:54:59.005 --> 00:55:02.341
Um. that's what you were thinking.

617
00:55:02.425 --> 00:55:03.384
No.

618
00:55:05.720 --> 00:55:09.015
I was thinking I was wrong.

619
00:55:09.098 --> 00:55:10.057
About what?

620
00:55:12.894 --> 00:55:15.521
All the death...

621
00:55:15.605 --> 00:55:16.731
all the shit.

622
00:55:19.275 --> 00:55:20.526
It doesn't really mean anything...

623
00:55:20.610 --> 00:55:21.944
to Frank and Hannah.
because—

624
00:55:25.072 --> 00:55:26.073
Well. she's got a dad...

625
00:55:26.157 --> 00:55:28.826
and he's got
his daughter. so—

626
00:55:28.910 --> 00:55:30.828
Cheeky monkey.

627
00:55:30.912 --> 00:55:32.121
I was wrong when I said...

628
00:55:32.205 --> 00:55:34.916
that staying alive
is as good as it gets.

629
00:55:38.586 --> 00:55:41.005
You see. that's what I was thinking.

630
00:55:41.088 --> 00:55:43.049
Was it?

631
00:55:43.132 --> 00:55:44.050
MmMmm.

632
00:55:44.133 --> 00:55:45.426
You stole my thought.

633
00:55:50.890 --> 00:55:53.601
Sorry.

634
00:55:53.684 --> 00:55:56.020
That's okay.
You keep it.

635
00:55:58.773 --> 00:55:59.690
Frank: It's getting late.

636
00:55:59.774 --> 00:56:01.651
Think we better stay here
for the night.

637
00:56:18.000 --> 00:56:20.461
Can't sleep.

638
00:56:20.545 --> 00:56:21.462
Me neither.

639
00:56:23.214 --> 00:56:25.675
Jim: Doesn't feel safe. does it?

640
00:56:25.758 --> 00:56:26.676
Outside like this.

641
00:56:28.761 --> 00:56:30.388
I think we're safe enough.

642
00:56:30.471 --> 00:56:34.559
Selena didn't seem
to have any trouble.

643
00:56:34.642 --> 00:56:35.810
Yeah. I noticed that.

644
00:56:37.144 --> 00:56:38.771
Hey. Selena.

645
00:56:38.854 --> 00:56:41.816
What? What is it?

646
00:56:41.899 --> 00:56:43.067
How did you get to sleep?

647
00:56:43.150 --> 00:56:44.485
Oh.

648
00:56:50.491 --> 00:56:51.409
Frank: Bloody hell.

649
00:56:51.492 --> 00:56:52.827
You must have needed...

650
00:56:52.910 --> 00:56:54.245
a hell of a prescription
for that lot.

651
00:56:54.328 --> 00:56:55.913
I didn't need a prescription.

652
00:56:55.997 --> 00:56:57.582
I qualified as a chemist.

653
00:56:57.665 --> 00:56:58.749
[Pills Rattle In Bottle]

654
00:56:58.833 --> 00:57:00.251
Jim: Oh. great. Valium.

655
00:57:00.334 --> 00:57:01.335
[Chuckles]

656
00:57:01.419 --> 00:57:04.171
Not only will we be able
to get to sleep...

657
00:57:04.255 --> 00:57:06.299
but if we're attacked
in the middle of the night...

658
00:57:06.382 --> 00:57:07.425
we won't even care.

659
00:57:07.508 --> 00:57:08.593
- [Rattles Pill Bottle]
- 2 each.

660
00:57:08.676 --> 00:57:10.344
No. not for me. thanks.

661
00:57:10.428 --> 00:57:12.430
Hannah: Can I. Dad?

662
00:57:12.513 --> 00:57:14.765
Frank: I don't think so. sweetheart.

663
00:57:14.849 --> 00:57:16.058
Please?

664
00:57:17.184 --> 00:57:18.102
No.

665
00:57:18.185 --> 00:57:19.437
I can't sleep.

666
00:57:22.273 --> 00:57:24.108
Jim: Come on. Frank.

667
00:57:24.191 --> 00:57:26.485
Let her live a little.

668
00:57:26.569 --> 00:57:27.903
Give her half of one.

669
00:57:27.987 --> 00:57:29.614
Jim: All right.
We're on.

670
00:57:29.697 --> 00:57:30.615
[Hannah Chuckles]

671
00:57:41.334 --> 00:57:42.251
Hannah: Night-night.

672
00:57:44.128 --> 00:57:45.713
Jim: You're a big softie. Frank.

673
00:57:47.548 --> 00:57:48.466
[Sighs]

674
00:58:17.244 --> 00:58:19.163
Frank?

675
00:58:19.246 --> 00:58:21.165
Hannah?

676
00:58:21.248 --> 00:58:22.249
Frank?

677
00:58:24.669 --> 00:58:26.587
[Sheep Bleat]

678
00:58:28.839 --> 00:58:30.049
Hello?

679
00:58:30.132 --> 00:58:32.051
Hello?

680
00:58:32.134 --> 00:58:33.344
Hello?

681
00:58:33.427 --> 00:58:34.845
Hello?

682
00:58:34.929 --> 00:58:35.888
Hello?

683
00:58:39.600 --> 00:58:41.560
[Mumbles]

684
00:58:44.021 --> 00:58:45.606
Frank: Shh.

685
00:58:47.400 --> 00:58:49.026
You're having a bad dream.
that's all.

686
00:58:52.822 --> 00:58:53.781
Thanks. Dad.

687
00:59:13.134 --> 00:59:15.094
[Birds Chirping]

688
00:59:25.980 --> 00:59:27.565
[Car Horn Honks]

689
00:59:27.648 --> 00:59:30.151
[Breathes Heavily]

690
00:59:30.234 --> 00:59:32.319
Come on. sleepyhead.

691
00:59:36.741 --> 00:59:38.576
Come on. Babe Ruth.

692
00:59:41.871 --> 00:59:42.830
Frank: Hurry up.

693
00:59:45.666 --> 00:59:46.584
Jim: Oh. no.

694
00:59:46.667 --> 00:59:47.626
Did I miss breakfast?

695
00:59:47.710 --> 00:59:49.086
Selena: You'll sleep
through anything. you.

696
00:59:49.170 --> 00:59:50.171
Jim: Did you have a fry-up?

697
00:59:50.254 --> 00:59:52.757
Frank: Maybe stop
at a pub along the way?

698
00:59:52.840 --> 00:59:53.758
Door.

699
01:00:15.404 --> 01:00:18.574
Man On Radio: ..We can feed you
and we can protect you.

700
01:00:18.657 --> 01:00:21.786
Our location is the 42nd Blockade...

701
01:00:21.869 --> 01:00:26.290
the M602. 27 miles northeast
of Manchester.

702
01:00:26.373 --> 01:00:28.459
You must find us. please.

703
01:00:28.542 --> 01:00:30.586
Salvation is here.

704
01:00:30.669 --> 01:00:33.547
The answer to infection is here.

705
01:00:41.138 --> 01:00:43.057
[Wind Whistles]

706
01:00:50.189 --> 01:00:51.440
- Sure?
-Yo.

707
01:01:05.704 --> 01:01:06.872
Must be Manchester.

708
01:01:10.084 --> 01:01:11.627
The whole of Manchester.

709
01:01:11.710 --> 01:01:12.670
The whole city.

710
01:01:15.548 --> 01:01:17.132
No fire crews to put it out.

711
01:01:41.198 --> 01:01:42.116
[Distant Explosion]

712
01:02:02.094 --> 01:02:04.013
[Car Approaches Slowly]

713
01:02:12.521 --> 01:02:15.149
42nd Blockade.

714
01:02:15.232 --> 01:02:16.150
This is it.

715
01:03:02.947 --> 01:03:03.864
[Shuts Off Engine]

716
01:03:16.710 --> 01:03:18.629
[Fire Crackles]

717
01:03:28.764 --> 01:03:30.891
I don't understand. Dad.

718
01:03:30.975 --> 01:03:32.309
Did they leave?

719
01:03:32.393 --> 01:03:33.394
I don't like this.

720
01:03:33.477 --> 01:03:34.561
I think we should go.

721
01:03:34.645 --> 01:03:35.562
No!

722
01:03:42.611 --> 01:03:43.612
Vehicles.

723
01:03:43.696 --> 01:03:44.613
We should check the vehicles.

724
01:03:44.697 --> 01:03:45.614
There has to be something.

725
01:04:05.551 --> 01:04:07.553
Nothing.

726
01:04:07.636 --> 01:04:09.138
Can't believe it.

727
01:04:09.221 --> 01:04:10.139
Selena: Frank.

728
01:04:11.682 --> 01:04:12.933
Frank.

729
01:04:15.936 --> 01:04:16.854
We have to go?

730
01:04:16.937 --> 01:04:17.855
Yeah.

731
01:04:17.938 --> 01:04:19.356
Go fucking where?!

732
01:04:21.650 --> 01:04:23.610
[Footsteps]

733
01:04:53.265 --> 01:04:54.349
[Cawing]

734
01:04:59.229 --> 01:05:00.272
Get out of it.

735
01:05:00.355 --> 01:05:02.316
[Crow Cawing]

736
01:05:05.152 --> 01:05:06.070
Get out of it.

737
01:05:13.535 --> 01:05:14.745
[Gate Rattles]

738
01:05:17.164 --> 01:05:18.082
[Gasps]

739
01:05:25.089 --> 01:05:26.590
Dad. are you all right?

740
01:05:27.800 --> 01:05:28.926
Yeah. I'm fine. sweetheart.

741
01:05:29.009 --> 01:05:31.178
[Breathes Rapidly]

742
01:05:31.261 --> 01:05:33.055
Sorry I lost my temper.

743
01:05:34.139 --> 01:05:36.266
Hannah.

744
01:05:36.350 --> 01:05:38.227
I love you very much.

745
01:05:38.310 --> 01:05:39.686
[Chuckles] What?

746
01:05:39.770 --> 01:05:41.438
Keep away from me.

747
01:05:41.522 --> 01:05:43.273
Stay where you are.

748
01:05:43.357 --> 01:05:44.316
- Ow.
- Dad?

749
01:05:44.399 --> 01:05:45.776
- Keep away from me!
- Dad?

750
01:05:45.859 --> 01:05:46.777
Keep away from me!

751
01:05:46.860 --> 01:05:48.278
- Keep away from me!
- Dad!

752
01:05:48.362 --> 01:05:50.280
- Keep away from me!
- Dad!

753
01:05:50.364 --> 01:05:52.616
Keep away!
Keep away!

754
01:05:52.699 --> 01:05:54.201
[Frank Screams]

755
01:05:54.284 --> 01:05:55.202
Hannah: What's wrong?

756
01:05:55.285 --> 01:05:56.787
Dad!

757
01:05:58.205 --> 01:05:59.206
[Screams]

758
01:06:00.374 --> 01:06:02.126
Jim!

759
01:06:02.209 --> 01:06:04.044
Jim. he's infected!

760
01:06:04.128 --> 01:06:05.045
Hannah: No! No!

761
01:06:05.129 --> 01:06:06.296
Selena: Jim!

762
01:06:06.380 --> 01:06:07.464
Jim. kill him!

763
01:06:07.548 --> 01:06:09.800
- Dad!
- Kill him!

764
01:06:09.883 --> 01:06:10.968
Kill him!

765
01:06:11.051 --> 01:06:12.594
[Gunshots]

766
01:06:19.726 --> 01:06:21.061
Stay away from him!

767
01:06:23.230 --> 01:06:24.940
Keep away from the body!

768
01:06:28.193 --> 01:06:29.444
Dad?

769
01:06:52.426 --> 01:06:55.262
Soldier: 3 survivors—
one male. 2 female.

770
01:06:55.345 --> 01:06:58.682
I repeat. one male. 2 female.

771
01:06:58.765 --> 01:07:01.518
<i>EVANS..</i>

772
01:07:01.602 --> 01:07:02.561
Put the kettle on.

773
01:07:51.860 --> 01:07:53.487
Man: I’m Major Henry West.

774
01:07:55.280 --> 01:07:56.198
Welcome.

775
01:07:56.281 --> 01:07:57.199
Jim.

776
01:07:57.282 --> 01:07:58.200
Hello. Jim.

777
01:07:59.576 --> 01:08:01.245
Hello.

778
01:08:03.497 --> 01:08:05.791
Well. we've got beds
with clean sheets...

779
01:08:05.874 --> 01:08:08.543
and a boiler
that produces hot water...

780
01:08:08.627 --> 01:08:10.921
so you can all have a shower.

781
01:08:11.004 --> 01:08:12.089
You look like you need one.

782
01:08:12.172 --> 01:08:13.131
Please.

783
01:08:16.343 --> 01:08:18.303
[Sobs Softly]

784
01:08:31.275 --> 01:08:34.319
[Soldiers Shouting]

785
01:08:34.403 --> 01:08:35.612
It ain't funny.

786
01:08:35.696 --> 01:08:37.447
I've got loads of cooking to do.

787
01:08:37.531 --> 01:08:38.865
Soldier: You fucking Doris.

788
01:08:38.949 --> 01:08:40.117
Please!

789
01:08:40.200 --> 01:08:41.285
Second Soldier: Run him over!

790
01:08:41.368 --> 01:08:42.703
I want to start cooking.

791
01:08:45.414 --> 01:08:46.331
Jim. Whispering: How's she doing?

792
01:08:46.415 --> 01:08:48.250
[Selena Laughs]

793
01:08:48.333 --> 01:08:49.793
Well. she's lost her dad. Jim.

794
01:08:49.876 --> 01:08:51.044
That's how she is.

795
01:08:53.880 --> 01:08:56.550
It's all fucked.

796
01:08:56.633 --> 01:08:57.551
What do you mean?

797
01:09:03.682 --> 01:09:05.100
No. don't do that.
Don't do that. Don't—

798
01:09:05.183 --> 01:09:06.310
Come on. come on. come on. come on.

799
01:09:06.393 --> 01:09:07.352
[Sobs]

800
01:09:07.436 --> 01:09:08.395
Hey. don't do that.

801
01:09:11.231 --> 01:09:13.025
Look. Hannah is
what Frank said she is. okay?

802
01:09:13.108 --> 01:09:14.818
She's tough. and she's strong...

803
01:09:14.901 --> 01:09:16.194
and she'll cope
just like I'll cope...

804
01:09:16.278 --> 01:09:17.237
and just like you'll cope.

805
01:09:17.321 --> 01:09:20.115
I don't want her
to have to fucking cope.

806
01:09:21.366 --> 01:09:23.910
I want her to be okay.

807
01:09:25.537 --> 01:09:27.664
When Hannah had her dad.
it was okay.

808
01:09:27.748 --> 01:09:30.500
It was okay for them.
and it was okay for us.

809
01:09:32.210 --> 01:09:33.837
[Sniffs]

810
01:09:33.920 --> 01:09:35.589
Now it's all just fucked.

811
01:09:39.760 --> 01:09:40.719
[Sighs]

812
01:10:07.913 --> 01:10:10.665
So you heard our broadcast?

813
01:10:10.749 --> 01:10:12.042
Yeah. we did.

814
01:10:12.125 --> 01:10:14.127
We must be a disappointment.

815
01:10:14.211 --> 01:10:15.629
You were hoping
for a full brigade...

816
01:10:15.712 --> 01:10:17.589
an army base with helicopters...

817
01:10:17.672 --> 01:10:18.882
and a field hospital.

818
01:10:22.803 --> 01:10:24.471
I was just hoping for—

819
01:10:24.554 --> 01:10:26.556
The answer to infection.

820
01:10:29.142 --> 01:10:30.560
Yeah.

821
01:10:30.644 --> 01:10:33.939
Well. as I said before. it's here...

822
01:10:34.022 --> 01:10:36.024
though it may not be
quite what you imagined.

823
01:10:36.108 --> 01:10:37.984
Just feel very lucky
to have found you.

824
01:10:38.068 --> 01:10:39.069
You were lucky.

825
01:10:39.152 --> 01:10:40.904
The fire drove
hundreds of infected...

826
01:10:40.987 --> 01:10:42.155
out of Manchester.

827
01:10:42.239 --> 01:10:44.324
The surrounding area
is teeming with them.

828
01:10:47.411 --> 01:10:48.370
But don't worry.

829
01:10:50.163 --> 01:10:51.331
You're quite safe here.

830
01:10:55.252 --> 01:10:57.921
West: Flat terrain
all around the house...

831
01:10:58.004 --> 01:10:58.964
floodlights...

832
01:10:59.047 --> 01:11:02.426
which we've rigged up
to a generator...

833
01:11:02.509 --> 01:11:05.095
high perimeter wall. which helps...

834
01:11:05.178 --> 01:11:06.596
and we've been lacing the ground...

835
01:11:06.680 --> 01:11:09.307
with trip wires and land mines.

836
01:11:09.391 --> 01:11:11.101
You wouldn't want to mow the lawn...

837
01:11:11.184 --> 01:11:12.769
but if they get in. we hear them.

838
01:11:17.691 --> 01:11:18.859
Secondary to protection...

839
01:11:18.942 --> 01:11:20.902
our real job is to rebuild...

840
01:11:20.986 --> 01:11:22.446
start again.

841
01:11:22.529 --> 01:11:23.864
The belly of the house...

842
01:11:23.947 --> 01:11:24.906
the heart.

843
01:11:24.990 --> 01:11:25.907
A wood-fired boiler...

844
01:11:25.991 --> 01:11:27.200
providing us with hot water...

845
01:11:27.284 --> 01:11:29.536
the first step towards civilization.

846
01:11:29.619 --> 01:11:30.912
The kitchen.

847
01:11:32.038 --> 01:11:33.248
Soldier: Here. I'll swap you.

848
01:11:33.331 --> 01:11:34.833
A bit of Kendal Mint Cake. right?

849
01:11:34.916 --> 01:11:36.042
Well. wait.
Now. don't be throwing it.

850
01:11:36.126 --> 01:11:37.043
Don't be—

851
01:11:38.295 --> 01:11:39.463
Now. don't be fighting.

852
01:11:39.546 --> 01:11:40.464
Will you put that back?

853
01:11:40.547 --> 01:11:42.132
Put it back.

854
01:11:42.215 --> 01:11:44.634
Jones. our resident tin-opener.

855
01:11:44.718 --> 01:11:46.219
What are you cooking. Jones?

856
01:11:46.303 --> 01:11:47.637
Surprise. sir.

857
01:11:47.721 --> 01:11:49.556
I can't wait.

858
01:11:57.898 --> 01:12:00.150
West: And lastly. meet Mailer.

859
01:12:00.233 --> 01:12:01.735
[Screams]

860
01:12:01.818 --> 01:12:03.278
[Mailer Chokes
On Chain]

861
01:12:03.361 --> 01:12:05.947
West: Mailer. Jim.

862
01:12:06.031 --> 01:12:07.782
Jim. Mailer.

863
01:12:07.866 --> 01:12:09.284
[Mailer Screams]

864
01:12:09.367 --> 01:12:11.077
Got infected 2 days ago.

865
01:12:12.245 --> 01:12:13.914
Mitchell managed
to knock him out cold...

866
01:12:13.997 --> 01:12:15.290
and we got a chain around his neck.

867
01:12:21.671 --> 01:12:22.672
You're keeping him alive?

868
01:12:24.925 --> 01:12:27.886
The idea was to learn
something about infection...

869
01:12:30.222 --> 01:12:31.264
have him teach me.

870
01:12:39.064 --> 01:12:40.148
And has he?

871
01:12:43.109 --> 01:12:44.069
In a way.

872
01:12:47.572 --> 01:12:48.615
[Mailer Screams]

873
01:12:51.785 --> 01:12:54.913
West: He's telling me
he'll never bake bread...

874
01:12:54.996 --> 01:12:57.123
plant crops...

875
01:12:57.207 --> 01:12:58.833
raise livestock.

876
01:12:58.917 --> 01:13:01.795
He's telling me he's future less...

877
01:13:06.633 --> 01:13:07.551
and eventually...

878
01:13:07.634 --> 01:13:09.386
he'll tell me how long
the infected take...

879
01:13:09.469 --> 01:13:10.387
to starve to death.

880
01:13:20.730 --> 01:13:22.649
[Mailer Breathing Heavily]

881
01:13:29.114 --> 01:13:31.575
[Screams]

882
01:13:31.658 --> 01:13:32.576
[Chain Snaps Tight]

883
01:13:35.787 --> 01:13:37.706
[Locks Door]

884
01:13:41.251 --> 01:13:42.419
[Soldier Bangs Table]

885
01:13:42.502 --> 01:13:44.754
Soldier: ♪» Will there be chips
or jacket spuds?

886
01:13:44.838 --> 01:13:47.757
<i>3 Will there be salad
or frozen peas?</i>

887
01:13:47.841 --> 01:13:48.758
[Soldier Bangs Table]

888
01:13:48.842 --> 01:13:50.093
♪ Will there be mushrooms? 2

889
01:13:50.176 --> 01:13:51.720
♪ Fried onion rings? gt

890
01:13:51.803 --> 01:13:54.264
Soldiers: ♪ You’ll have
to wait and see

891
01:13:54.347 --> 01:13:56.600
< Hope it’s chips.
it’s chips ♪

